FixFieldSpec.Name: Account
FixFieldSpec.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between broker and institution.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AdvId
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AdvRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AdvSide
FixFieldSpec.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade Valid values: B = Buy S = Sell X = Cross T = Trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: AdvTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type Valid values: N = New C = Cancel R = Replace

FixFieldSpec.Name: AvgPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BeginSeqNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

FixFieldSpec.Name: BeginString
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Valid values: FIX.4.2

FixFieldSpec.Name: BodyLength
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CheckSum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Appendix B: CheckSum Calculation for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClOrdID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by institution (identified by SenderCompID or OnBehalfOfCompID as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods,should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Commission
FixFieldSpec.Description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CommType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Commission type Valid values: 1 = per share 2 = percentage 3 = absolute

FixFieldSpec.Name: CumQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of shares filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Currency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See Appendix A: Valid Currency Codes for information on obtaining valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EndSeqNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = “0” (representing infinity).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by broker (will be 0 (zero) for ExecTransType=3 (Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space. Valid values: 1 = Not held 2 = Work 3 = Go along 4 = Over the day 5 = Held 6 = Participate don't initiate 7 = Strict scale 8 = Try to scale 9 = Stay on bidside 0 = Stay on offerside A = No cross (cross is forbidden) B = OK to cross C = Call first D = Percent of volume “(indicates that the sender does not want to be all of the volume on the floor vs. a specific percentage)” E = Do not increase - DNI F = Do not reduce - DNR G = All or none - AON I = Institutions only L = Last peg (last sale) M = Mid-price peg (midprice of inside quote) N = Non-negotiable O = Opening pegP = Market peg R = Primary peg (primary market - buy at bid/sell at offer) S = Suspend T = Fixed Peg to Local best bid or offer at time of order U = Customer Display Instruction (Rule11Ac1-1/4) V = Netting (for Forex) W = Peg to VWAP

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Cancel 2 = Correct 3 = Status

FixFieldSpec.Name: HandlInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor Valid values: 1 = Automated execution order, private, no Broker intervention 2 = Automated execution order, public, Broker intervention OK 3 = Manual order, best execution

FixFieldSpec.Name: IDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies class of alternative SecurityID Valid values: 1 = CUSIP 2 = SEDOL 3 = QUIK 4 = ISIN number 5 = RIC code 6 = ISO Currency Code 7 = ISO Country Code 8 = Exchange Symbol 9 = Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format) 100+ are reserved for private security identifications

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOIid
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOIQltyInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Relative quality of indication Valid values: L = Low M = Medium H = High

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOIRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOIShares
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares in numeric or relative size. Valid values: 0 - 1000000000 S = Small M = Medium L = Large

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOITransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type Valid values: N = New C = Cancel R = Replace

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastCapacity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Broker capacity in order execution Valid values: 1 = Agent 2 = Cross as agent 3 = Cross as principal 4 = Principal

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastMkt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Market of execution for last fill Valid values: See Appendix C

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price of this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastShares
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of shares bought/sold on this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LinesOfText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

FixFieldSpec.Name: MsgSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Integer message sequence number.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MsgType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U1, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver. Valid values: *** Note the use of lower case letters *** 0 = Heartbeat 1 = Test Request 2 = Resend Request 3 = Reject 4 = Sequence Reset 5 = Logout 6 = Indication of Interest 7 = Advertisement 8 = Execution Report 9 = Order Cancel Reject A = Logon B = News C = Email D = Order – Single E = Order – List F = Order Cancel Request G= Order Cancel/Replace Request H= Order Status Request J = Allocation K = List Cancel Request L = List Execute M = List Status Request N = List Status P = Allocation ACK Q = Don’t Know Trade (DK) R = Quote Request S = Quote T = Settlement Instructions V = Market Data Request W = Market Data-Snapshot/Full Refresh X = Market Data-Incremental Refresh Y = Market Data Request Reject Z = Quote Cancel a = Quote Status Request b = Quote Acknowledgement c = Security Definition Request d = Security Definition e = Security Status Request f = Security Status g = Trading Session Status Request h = Trading Session Status i = Mass Quote j = Business Message Reject k = Bid Request l = Bid Response (lowercase L) m = List Strike Price

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewSeqNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: New sequence number

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or based on normal convention the number of contracts for options, futures, convertible bonds, etc. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrdStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies current status of order. Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Partially filled 2 = Filled 3 = Done for day 4 = Canceled 5 = Replaced 6 = Pending Cancel (e.g. result of Order Cancel Request) 7 = Stopped 8 = Rejected 9 = Suspended A = Pending New B = Calculated C = Expired D = Accepted for bidding E = Pending Replace (e.g. result of Order Cancel/Replace Request)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrdType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Order type. Valid values: 1 = Market 2 = Limit 3 = Stop 4 = Stop limit 5 = Market on close 6 = With or without 7 = Limit or better 8 = Limit with or without 9 = On basis A = On close B = Limit on close C =Forex - Market D = Previously quoted E = Previously indicated F = Forex - Limit G = Forex - Swap H = Forex - Previously Quoted I = Funari (Limit Day Order with unexecuted portion handled as Market On Close. e.g. Japan) P = Pegged

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigClOrdID
FixFieldSpec.Description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”))

FixFieldSpec.Name: PossDupFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number Valid values: Y = Possible duplicate N = Original transmission

FixFieldSpec.Name: Price
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price per share

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference message sequence number

FixFieldSpec.Name: RelatdSym
FixFieldSpec.Description: Symbol of issue related to story. Can be repeated within message to identify multiple companies.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Rule80A
FixFieldSpec.Description: Note that the name of this field is changing to “OrderCapacity” as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. . See the “Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market” appendix for market-specific usage of this field.Valid values: A = Agency single order B = Short exempt transaction (refer to A type) C = Program Order, non-index arb, for Member firm/org D = Program Order, index arb, for Member firm/org E = Registered Equity Market Maker trades F = Short exempt transaction (refer to W type) H = Short exempt transaction (refer to I type) I = Individual Investor, single order J = Program Order, index arb, for individual customer K = Program Order, non-index arb, for individual customer L = Short exempt transaction for member competing market-maker affiliated with the firm clearing the trade (refer to P and O types) M = Program Order, index arb, for other member N = Program Order, non-index arb, for other member O = Competing dealer trades P = Principal R = Competing dealer trades S = Specialist trades T = Competing dealer trades U = Program Order, index arb, for other agency W = All other orders as agent for other member X = Short exempt transaction for member competing market-maker not affiliated with the firm clearing the trade (refer to W and T types) Y = Program Order, non-index arb, for other agency Z = Short exempt transaction for non-member competing market-maker (refer to A and R types)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: CUSIP or other alternate security identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: SenderCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SenderSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SendingTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Shares
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Side
FixFieldSpec.Description: Side of order Valid values: 1 = Buy 2 = Sell 3 = Buy minus 4 = Sell plus 5 = Sell short 6 = Sell short exempt 7 = Undisclosed (valid for IOI and List Order messages only) 8 = Cross (orders where counterparty is an exchange, valid for all messages except IOIs) 9 = Cross short

FixFieldSpec.Name: Symbol
FixFieldSpec.Description: Ticker symbol

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. “ADMIN” reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Text
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TimeInForce
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. Valid values: 0 = Day 1 = Good Till Cancel (GTC) 2 = At the Opening (OPG) 3 = Immediate or Cancel (IOC) 4 = Fill or Kill (FOK) 5 = Good Till Crossing (GTX) 6 = Good Till Date

FixFieldSpec.Name: TransactTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Urgency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Urgency flag Valid values: 0 = Normal 1 = Flash 2 = Background

FixFieldSpec.Name: ValidUntilTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlmntTyp
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates order settlement period. Absence of this field is interpreted as Regular. Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution. Valid values: 0 = Regular 1 = Cash 2 = Next Day 3 = T+2 4 = T+3 5 = T+4 6 = Future 7 = When Issued 8 = Sellers Option 9 = T+ 5

FixFieldSpec.Name: FutSettDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. Required when SettlmntTyp = 6 (Future) or SettlmntTyp = 8 (Sellers Option). (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SymbolSfx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType. Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListSeqNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of ListNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoOrders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation. (formerly named: ListNoOrds) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListExecInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel 3 = Preliminary (without MiscFees and NetMoney) 4 = Calculated (includes MiscFees and NetMoney) 5 = Calculated without Preliminary (sent unsolicited by broker, includes MiscFees and NetMoney)

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefAllocID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier to be used with Replace, Cancel, and Calculated AllocTransType messages. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoOrders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AvgPrxPrecision
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecBroker
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies executing / give-up broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OpenClose
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together. Valid Values: O=Open C=Close

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoAllocs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating AllocAccount/AllocPrice entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocAccount
FixFieldSpec.Description: Sub-account mnemonic

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocShares
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ProcessCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount / AllocPrice/AllocShares / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade. Valid values: 0 = regular 1 = soft dollar 2 = step-in 3 = step-out 4 = soft-dollar step-in 5 = soft-dollar step-out 6 = plan sponsor

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRpts
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of reports within series.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RptSeq
FixFieldSpec.Description: Sequence number of message within report series.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CxlQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of shares canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies status of allocation. Valid values: 0 = accepted (successfully processed) 1 = rejected 2 = partial accept 3 = received (received, not yet processed)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocRejCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies reason for rejection. Valid values: 0 = unknown account(s) 1 = incorrect quantity 2 = incorrect average price 3 = unknown executing broker mnemonic 4 = commission difference 5 = unknown OrderID 6 = unknown ListID 7 = other

FixFieldSpec.Name: Signature
FixFieldSpec.Description: Electronic signature

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecureDataLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Length of encrypted message

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecureData
FixFieldSpec.Description: Actual encrypted data stream

FixFieldSpec.Name: BrokerOfCredit
FixFieldSpec.Description: Broker to receive trade credit.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SignatureLength
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of bytes in signature field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EmailType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Email message type. Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Reply 2 = Admin Reply

FixFieldSpec.Name: RawDataLength
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RawData
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PossResend
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number. Valid Values: Y=Possible resend N=Original transmission

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncryptMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Method of encryption. Valid values: 0 = None / other 1 = PKCS (proprietary) 2 = DES (ECB mode) 3 = PKCS/DES (proprietary) 4 = PGP/DES (defunct) 5 = PGP/DES-MD5 (see app note on FIX web site) 6 = PEM/DES-MD5 (see app note on FIX web site)

FixFieldSpec.Name: StopPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price per share

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExDestination
FixFieldSpec.Description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See Appendix C

FixFieldSpec.Name: CxlRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection. Valid values: 0 = Too late to cancel 1 = Unknown order 2 = Broker Option 3 = Order already in Pending Cancel or Pending Replace status

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrdRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for order rejection. Valid values: 0 = Broker option 1 = Unknown symbol 2 = Exchange closed 3 = Order exceeds limit 4 = Too late to enter 5 = Unknown Order 6 = Duplicate Order (e.g. dupe ClOrdID) 7 = Duplicate of a verbally communicated order 8 = Stale Order

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOIQualifier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to qualify IOI use. Valid values: A = All or none C = At the close I = In touch with L = Limit M = More behind O = At the open P = Taking a position Q = At the Market (previously called Current Quote) R = Ready to trade S = Portfolio show-n T = Through the day V = Versus W = Indication - Working away X = Crossing opportunity Y = At the Midpoint Z = Pre-open

FixFieldSpec.Name: WaveNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier to aid in the management of multiple lists derived from a single, master list.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Issuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Company name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Security description.

FixFieldSpec.Name: HeartBtInt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClientID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Firm identifier used in third party-transactions (should not be a substitute for OnBehalfOfCompID/DeliverToCompID).

FixFieldSpec.Name: MinQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxFloor
FixFieldSpec.Description: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TestReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

FixFieldSpec.Name: ReportToExch
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting. Valid values: Y = Indicates that party receiving message must report trade N = Indicates that party sending message will report trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: LocateReqd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.Valid values: Y = Indicates the broker is responsible for locating the stock N = Indicates the broker is not required to locate

FixFieldSpec.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for quote

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetMoney
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ForexReq
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction. Valid values: Y = Execute Forex after security trade N = Do not execute Forex after security trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigSendingTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”) when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: GapFillFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent. Valid values: Y = Gap Fill message, MsgSeqNum field valid N = Sequence Reset, ignore MsgSeqNum

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoExecs
FixFieldSpec.Description: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExpireTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DKReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for execution rejection. Valid values: A = Unknown symbol B = Wrong side C = Quantity exceeds order D = No matching order E = Price exceeds limit Z = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliverToCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliverToSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

FixFieldSpec.Name: IOINaturalFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity. Valid values: Y = Natural N = Not natural

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for quote request

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid price/rate

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer price/rate

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of bid (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of offer (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMiscFees
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

FixFieldSpec.Name: MiscFeeAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Miscellaneous fee value

FixFieldSpec.Name: MiscFeeCurr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency of miscellaneous fee

FixFieldSpec.Name: MiscFeeType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates type of miscellaneous fee. Valid values: 1 = Regulatory (e.g. SEC) 2 = Tax 3 = Local Commission 4 = Exchange Fees 5 = Stamp 6 = Levy 7 = Other 8 = Markup 9 = Consumption Tax

FixFieldSpec.Name: PrevClosePx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Previous closing price of security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ResetSeqNumFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers. Valid values: Y = Yes, reset sequence numbers N = No

FixFieldSpec.Name: SenderLocationID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetLocationID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliverToLocationID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRelatedSym
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Subject
FixFieldSpec.Description: The subject of an Email message

FixFieldSpec.Name: Headline
FixFieldSpec.Description: The headline of a News message

FixFieldSpec.Name: URLLink
FixFieldSpec.Description: A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://www.XYZ.com/research.html)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes the specific ExecutionRpt (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled) Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Partial fill 2 = Fill 3 = Done for day 4 = Canceled 5 = Replace 6 = Pending Cancel (e.g. result of Order Cancel Request) 7 = Stopped 8 = Rejected 9 = Suspended A = Pending New B = Calculated C = Expired D = Restated (ExecutionRpt sent unsolicited by sellside, with ExecRestatementReason set) E = Pending Replace (e.g. result of Order Cancel/Replace Request)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LeavesQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of shares open for further execution. If the OrdStatus is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty - CumQty. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashOrderQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as a number of shares. The broker would be responsible for converting and calculating a share quantity (OrderQty) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocAvgPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: AvgPx for a specific AllocAccount

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocNetMoney
FixFieldSpec.Description: NetMoney for a specific AllocAccount

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrFxRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt from Currency to SettlCurrency

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate should be multiplied or divided. M=Multiply D=Divide

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumDaysInterest
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

FixFieldSpec.Name: AccruedInterestRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Accrued Interest Rate for convertible bonds and fixed income

FixFieldSpec.Name: AccruedInterestAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstMode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions Valid values: 0 = Default 1 = Standing Instructions Provided 2 = Specific Allocation Account Overriding 3 = Specific Allocation Account Standing

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instructions message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Settlement Instructions message transaction type Valid values: N = New C = Cancel R = Replace

FixFieldSpec.Name: EmailThreadID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates source of Settlement Instructions Valid values: 1 = Broker’s Instructions 2 = Institution’s Instructions

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlLocation
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies Settlement Depository or Country Code (ISITC spec) Valid values: CED = CEDEL DTC = Depository Trust Company EUR = Euroclear FED = Federal Book Entry PNY= Physical PTC = Participant Trust Company ISO Country Code = Local Market Settle Location

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates type of security (ISITC spec) Valid values: BA = Bankers Acceptance CB = Convertible Bond (Note not part of ISITC spec) CD = Certificate Of Deposit CMO = Collateralize Mortgage Obligation CORP = Corporate Bond CP = Commercial Paper CPP = Corporate Private Placement CS = Common Stock FHA = Federal Housing Authority FHL = Federal Home Loan FN = Federal National Mortgage Association FOR = Foreign Exchange Contract FUT = Future GN = Government National Mortgage Association GOVT = Treasuries + Agency Debenture IET Mortgage IOETTE MF = Mutual Fund MIO = Mortgage Interest Only MPO = Mortgage Principal Only MPP = Mortgage Private Placement MPT = Miscellaneous Pass-Thru MUNI = Municipal Bond NONE = No ISITC Security Type OPT = Option PS = Preferred Stock RP = Repurchase Agreement RVRP = Reverse Repurchase Agreement SL = Student Loan Marketing Association TD = Time Deposit USTB = US Treasury Bill WAR = Warrant ZOO = Cats, Tigers & Lions (a real code: US Treasury Receipts) ? = “Wildcard” entry (used on Security Definition Request message)

FixFieldSpec.Name: EffectiveTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: StandInstDbType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used Valid values: 0 = Other 1 = DTC SID 2 = Thomson ALERT 3 = A Global Custodian (StandInstDbName must be provided)

FixFieldSpec.Name: StandInstDbName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (i.e. the Global Custodian’s name).

FixFieldSpec.Name: StandInstDbID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlDeliveryType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies type of settlement 0 = “Versus. Payment”: Deliver (if Sell) or Receive (if Buy) vs. (Against) Payment 1 = “Free”: Deliver (if Sell) or Receive (if Buy) Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlDepositoryCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Broker’s account code at the depository (i.e. CEDEL ID for CEDEL, FINS for DTC, or Euroclear ID for Euroclear) if SettlLocation is a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlBrkrCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the broker involved (i.e. for multi-company brokerage firms)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the institution involved (i.e. for multi-company institution firms)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactPhone
FixFieldSpec.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentContactName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashSettlAgentContactPhone
FixFieldSpec.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidSpotRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid F/X spot rate.y vary and not limited to four)

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferSpotRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer F/X spot rate.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderQty2
FixFieldSpec.Description: OrderQty of the future part of a F/X swap order.

FixFieldSpec.Name: FutSettDate2
FixFieldSpec.Description: FutSettDate of the future part of a F/X swap order.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastSpotRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: F/X spot rate.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastForwardPoints
FixFieldSpec.Description: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate. May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocLinkID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID) together, i.e. for F/X “Netting” or “Swaps”. Should be unique.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocLinkType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID is used. Valid values: 0 = F/X Netting 1 = F/X Swap

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryOrderID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID used by an exchange or executing system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoIOIQualifiers
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaturityMonthYear
FixFieldSpec.Description: Month and Year of the maturity for SecurityType=FUT or SecurityType=OPT. Required if MaturityDay is specified. Format: YYYYMM (i.e. 199903)

FixFieldSpec.Name: PutOrCall
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether an Option is for a put or call. Valid values: 0 = Put 1 = Call

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikePrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Strike Price for an Option.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CoveredOrUncovered
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used for options Valid values: 0 = Covered 1 = Uncovered

FixFieldSpec.Name: CustomerOrFirm
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used for options when delivering the order to an execution system/exchange to specify if the order is for a customer or the firm placing the order itself. Valid values: 0 = Customer 1 = Firm

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaturityDay
FixFieldSpec.Description: Day of month used in conjunction with MaturityMonthYear to specify the maturity date for SecurityType=FUT or SecurityType=OPT. Valid values: 1-31

FixFieldSpec.Name: OptAttribute
FixFieldSpec.Description: Can be used for SecurityType=OPT to identify a particular security. Valid values vary by SecurityExchange: For Exchange: MONEP (Paris) L = Long (a.k.a. “American”) S = Short (a.k.a. “European”) For Exchanges: DTB (Frankfurt), HKSE (Hong Kong), and SOFFEX (Zurich) 0-9 = single digit “version” number assigned by exchange following capital adjustments (0=current, 1=prior, 2=prior to 1, etc).

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityExchange
FixFieldSpec.Description: Market used to help identify a security. Valid values: See Appendix C

FixFieldSpec.Name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker). Valid values: Y = Details should be communicated N = Details should not be communicated

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocHandlInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation message should handle/process the account details. Valid values: 1 = Match 2 = Forward 3 = Forward and Match

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxShow
FixFieldSpec.Description: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegDifference
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount (signed) added to the price of the peg for a pegged order.

FixFieldSpec.Name: XmlDataLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Length of the XmlData data block.

FixFieldSpec.Name: XmlData
FixFieldSpec.Description: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType transaction types.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRoutingIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID and RoutingType values. See Appendix L – Pre-Trade Message Targeting/Routing

FixFieldSpec.Name: RoutingType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of RoutingID specified. Valid values: 1 = Target Firm 2 = Target List 3 = Block Firm 4 = Block List

FixFieldSpec.Name: RoutingID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SpreadToBenchmark
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income. Basis points relative to a benchmark. To be expressed as "count of basis points" (vs. an absolute value). E.g. High Grade Corporate Bonds may express price as basis points relative to benchmark (the Benchmark field). Note: Basis points can be negative.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Benchmark
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income. Identifies the benchmark (e.g. used in conjunction with the SpreadToBenchmark field). Valid values: 1 = CURVE 2 = 5-YR 3 = OLD-5 4 = 10-YR 5 = OLD-10 6 = 30-YR 7 = OLD-30 8 = 3-MO-LIBOR 9 = 6-MO-LIBOR

FixFieldSpec.Name: CouponRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income. Coupon rate of the bond. Will be zero for step-up bonds.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContractMultiplier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the ratio or multiply factor to convert from contracts to shares (e.g. 1.0, 100, 1000, etc). Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc. Note: If used, quantities should be expressed in the "nominal" (e.g. contracts vs. shares) amount.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Market Data Request

FixFieldSpec.Name: SubscriptionRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Subscription Request Type Valid values: 0 = Snapshot 1 = Snapshot + Updates (Subscribe) 2 = Disable previous Snapshot + Update Request (Unsubscribe)

FixFieldSpec.Name: MarketDepth
FixFieldSpec.Description: Depth of market for Book Snapshot Valid values: 0 = Full Book 1 = Top of Book N>1 = Report best N price tiers of data

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDUpdateType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the type of Market Data update. Valid values: 0 = Full Refresh 1 = Incremental Refresh

FixFieldSpec.Name: AggregatedBook
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies whether or not book entries should be aggregated. Valid values: Y = one book entry per side per price N = Multiple entries per side per price allowed (Not specified) = broker option

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMDEntryTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of MDEntryType fields requested.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMDEntries
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of entries in Market Data message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type Market Data entry. Valid values: 0 = Bid 1 = Offer 2 = Trade 3 = Index Value 4 = Opening Price 5 = Closing Price 6 = Settlement Price 7 = Trading Session High Price 8 = Trading Session Low Price 9 = Trading Session VWAP Price

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price of the Market Data Entry.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntrySize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares represented by the Market Data Entry.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of Market Data Entry.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of Market Data Entry.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TickDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: Direction of the "tick". Valid values: 0 = Plus Tick 1 = Zero-Plus Tick 2 = Minus Tick 3 = Zero-Minus Tick

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDMkt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Market posting quote / trade. Valid values: See Appendix C

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteCondition
FixFieldSpec.Description: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a quote. Valid values: A = Open / Active B = Closed / Inactive C = Exchange Best D = Consolidated Best E = Locked F = Crossed G = Depth H = Fast Trading I = Non-Firm

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeCondition
FixFieldSpec.Description: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a trade Valid values: A = Cash (only) Market B = Average Price Trade C = Cash Trade (same day clearing) D = Next Day (only) Market E = Opening / Reopening Trade Detail F = Intraday Trade Detail G = Rule 127 Trade (NYSE) H = Rule 155 Trade (Amex) I = Sold Last (late reporting) J = Next Day Trade (next day clearing) K = Opened (late report of opened trade) L = Seller M = Sold (out of sequence) N = Stopped Stock (guarantee of price but does not execute the order)

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique Market Data Entry identifier.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDUpdateAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Market Data update action. Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Change 2 = Delete

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Refers to a previous MDEntryID.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDReqRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for the rejection of a Market Data request. Valid values: 0 = Unknown symbol 1 = Duplicate MDReqID 2 = Insufficient Bandwidth 3 = Insufficient Permissions 4 = Unsupported SubscriptionRequestType 5 = Unsupported MarketDepth 6 = Unsupported MDUpdateType 7 = Unsupported AggregatedBook 8 = Unsupported MDEntryType

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryOriginator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Originator of a Market Data Entry

FixFieldSpec.Name: LocationID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identification of a Market Maker’s location

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeskID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identification of a Market Maker’s desk

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeleteReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for deletion. Valid values: 0 = Cancelation / Trade Bust 1 = Error

FixFieldSpec.Name: OpenCloseSettleFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Flag that identifies a price. Valid values: 0 = Daily Open / Close / Settlement price 1 = Session Open / Close / Settlement price 2 = Delivery Settlement price

FixFieldSpec.Name: SellerDays
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the number of days that may elapse before delivery of the security

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryBuyer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Buying party in a trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntrySeller
FixFieldSpec.Description: Selling party in a trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDEntryPositionNo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Display position of a bid or offer, numbered from most competitive to least competitive, per market side, beginning with 1.

FixFieldSpec.Name: FinancialStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies a firm’s financial status. Valid values: 1 = Bankrupt

FixFieldSpec.Name: CorporateAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of Corporate Action. Valid values: A = Ex-Dividend B = Ex-Distribution C = Ex-Rights D = New E = Ex-Interest

FixFieldSpec.Name: DefBidSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Default Bid Size.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DefOfferSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Default Offer Size.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoQuoteEntries
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoQuoteSets
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of sets of quotes in the message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteAckStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the status of the quote acknowledgement. Valid values: 0-Accepted 1-Canceled for Symbol(s) 2-Canceled for Security Type(s) 3-Canceled for Underlying 4-Canceled All 5-Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteCancelType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of quote cancel. Valid Values: 1 – Cancel for Symbol(s) 2 – Cancel for Security Type(s) 3 – Cancel for Underlying Symbol 4 – Cancel All Quotes

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteEntryID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Uniquely identifies the quote as part of a QuoteSet.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Quote was rejected: Valid Values: 1 = Unknown symbol (Security) 2 = Exchange(Security) closed 3 = Quote Request exceeds limit 4 = Too late to enter 5 = Unknown Quote 6 = Duplicate Quote 7 = Invalid bid/ask spread 8 = Invalid price 9 = Not authorized to quote security

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteResponseLevel
FixFieldSpec.Description: Level of Response requested from receiver of quote messages. Valid Values: 0 – No Acknowledgement (Default) 1 – Acknowledge only negative or erroneous quotes 2 – Acknowledge each quote messages

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteSetID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique id for the Quote Set.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of Quote Request being generated Valid values: 1-Manual 2-Automatic

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotQuoteEntries
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of quotes for the quote set across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoQuoteEntries in each message that has repeating quotes that are part of the same quote set.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s IDSource. Valid values: see IDSource field

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s Issuer. See Issuer field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityDesc. See SecurityDesc field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityExchange
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityExchange. Can be used to identify the underlying security. Valid values: see SecurityExchange

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityID. See SecurityID field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SecurityType. Valid values: see SecurityType field

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSymbol
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s Symbol. See Symbol field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSymbolSfx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingMaturityMonthYear
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s MaturityMonthYear. Required if UnderlyingMaturityDay is specified. See MaturityMonthYear field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDay
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s MaturityDay. See MaturityDay field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingPutOrCall
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s PutOrCall. See PutOrCall field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStrikePrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s StrikePrice. See StrikePrice field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingOptAttribute
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s OptAttribute. See OptAttribute field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s Currency. See Currency field for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: RatioQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of a particular leg in the security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Security Definition Request. Valid values: 0 = Request Security identity and specifications 1 = Request Security identity for the specifications provided (Name of the security is not supplied) 2 = Request List Security Types 3 = Request List Securities (Can be qualified with Symbol, SecurityType, TradingSessionID, SecurityExchange is provided then only list Securities for the specific type)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityResponseID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID of a Security Definition message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityResponseType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Security Definition message response. Valid values: 1 = Accept security proposal as is 2 = Accept security proposal with revisions as indicated in the message 3 = List of security types returned per request 4 = List of securities returned per request 5 = Reject security proposal 6 = Can not match selection criteria

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityStatusReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID of a Security Status Request message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnsolicitedIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not message is being sent as a result of a subscription request or not. Valid values: Y = Message is being sent unsolicited N = Message is being sent as a result of a prior request

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityTradingStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the trading status applicable to the transaction. Valid values: 1 = Opening Delay 2 = Trading Halt 3 = Resume 4 = No Open/No Resume 5 = Price Indication 6 = Trading Range Indication 7 = Market Imbalance Buy 8 = Market Imbalance Sell 9 = Market On Close Imbalance Buy 10 = Market On Close Imbalance Sell 11 = (not assigned) 12 = No Market Imbalance 13 = No Market On Close Imbalance 14 = ITS Pre-Opening 15 = New Price Indication 16 = Trade Dissemination Time 17 = Ready to trade (start of session) 18 = Not Available for trading (end of session) 19 = Not Traded on this Market 20 = Unknown or Invalid

FixFieldSpec.Name: HaltReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading Halt. Valid values: I = Order Imbalance X = Equipment Changeover P = News Pending D = News Dissemination E = Order Influx M = Additional Information

FixFieldSpec.Name: InViewOfCommon
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to Common Stock trading being halted. Valid values: Y = Halt was due to common stock being halted N = Halt was not related to a halt of the common stock

FixFieldSpec.Name: DueToRelated
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to the Related Security being halted. Valid values: Y = Halt was due to related security being halted N = Halt was not related to a halt of the related security

FixFieldSpec.Name: BuyVolume
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares bought.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SellVolume
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of shares sold.

FixFieldSpec.Name: HighPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Represents an indication of the high end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

FixFieldSpec.Name: LowPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Represents an indication of the low end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

FixFieldSpec.Name: Adjustment
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of adjustment. Valid values: 1 = Cancel 2 = Error 3 = Correction

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradingSessionID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier for Trading Session Can be used to represent a specific market trading session (e.g. “PRE-OPEN", "CROSS_2", "AFTER-HOURS", "TOSTNET1", "TOSTNET2", etc). Values should be bi-laterally agreed to between counterparties.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraTrader
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the trader (e.g. "badge number") of the ContraBroker.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Method of trading Valid values: 1 = Electronic 2 = Open Outcry 3 = Two Party

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesMode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Trading Session Mode Valid values: 1 = Testing 2 = Simulated 3 = Production

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: State of the trading session. Valid values: 1 = Halted 2 = Open 3 = Closed 4 = Pre-Open 5 = Pre-Close

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesStartTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Starting time of the trading session

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesOpenTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of the opening of the trading session

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesPreCloseTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time of the pre-closed of the trading session

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesCloseTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Closing time of the trading session

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesEndTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: End time of the trading session

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumberOfOrders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of orders in the market.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MessageEncoding
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of message encoding (non-ASCII (non-English) characters) used in a message’s “Encoded” fields. Valid values: ISO-2022-JP (for using JIS) EUC-JP (for using EUC) Shift_JIS (for using SJIS) UTF-8 (for using Unicode)

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedIssuerLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedIssuer field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Issuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Issuer field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSecurityDescLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListExecInstLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListExecInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSubjectLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSubject
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedHeadlineLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedHeadline
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedAllocTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedAllocText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Executed price for an AllocAccount entry used when using “executed price” vs. “average price” allocations (e.g. Japan).

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteEntryRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Quote Entry was rejected: Valid values: 1 = Unknown symbol (Security) 2 = Exchange(Security) closed 3 = Quote exceeds limit 4 = Too late to enter 5 = Unknown Quote 6 = Duplicate Quote 7 = Invalid bid/ask spread 8 = Invalid price 9 = Not authorized to quote security

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
FixFieldSpec.Description: The last MsgSeqNum value received and processed. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OnBehalfOfSendingTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used when a message is sent via a “hub” or “service bureau”. If A sends to Q (the hub) who then sends to B via a separate FIX session, then when Q sends to B the value of this field should represent the SendingTime on the message A sent to Q. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefTagID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefMsgType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The MsgType of the FIX message being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SessionRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message. Valid values: 0 = Invalid tag number 1 = Required tag missing 2 = Tag not defined for this message type 3 = Undefined Tag 4 = Tag specified without a value 5 = Value is incorrect (out of range) for this tag 6 = Incorrect data format for value 7 = Decryption problem 8 = Signature problem 9 = CompID problem 10 = SendingTime accuracy problem 11 = Invalid MsgType

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidRequestTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the Bid Request message type. Valid values: N = New C = Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraBroker
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplianceID
FixFieldSpec.Description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

FixFieldSpec.Name: SolicitedFlag
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited. Valid values: Y = Was solcitied N = Was not solicited

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecRestatementReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for an ExecutionRpt message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel. Valid values: 0 = GT Corporate action 1 = GT renewal / restatement (no corporate action) 2 = Verbal change 3 = Repricing of order 4 = Broker option 5 = Partial decline of OrderQty (e.g. exchange-initiated partial cancel)

FixFieldSpec.Name: BusinessRejectRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The value of the business-level “ID” field on the message being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BusinessRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message. Valid values: 0 = Other 1 = Unkown ID 2 = Unknown Security 3 = Unsupported Message Type 4 = Application not available 5 = Conditionally Required Field Missing

FixFieldSpec.Name: GrossTradeAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty * AvgPx) expressed in units of currency.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoContraBrokers
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of ContraBroker entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxMessageSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMsgTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of MsgTypes in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MsgDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the direction of the messsage. Valid values: S = Send R = Receive

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoTradingSessions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of TradingSessionIDs in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalVolumeTraded
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total volume (quantity) traded.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffset is related to and should be mathematically added to. Valid values: 0 = Related to displayed price 1 = Related to market price 2 = Related to primary price 3 = Related to local primary price 4 = Related to midpoint price 5 = Related to last trade price

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionOffset
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount (signed) added to the “related to” price specified via DiscretionInst.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClientBidID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Descriptive name for list order.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalNumSecurities
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of securities.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request. Valid values: 1 – “Non Disclosed” Style (e.g. US/European) 2 – “Disclosed” Style (e.g. Japanese) 3 – No Bidding Process

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumTickets
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of tickets.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValue1
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amounts in currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValue2
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amounts in currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoBidDescriptors
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of BidDescriptor entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidDescriptorType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor. Valid values: 1 – Sector 2 – Country 3 – Index

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidDescriptor
FixFieldSpec.Description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorType. If BidDescriptorType =1 Industrials etc – Free text If BidDescriptorType =2 "FR" etc – ISO Country Codes If BidDescriptorType =3 FT100, FT250, STOX – Free text

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValueInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell. Valid values: 1 – SideValue1 2 – SideValue 2

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityPctLow
FixFieldSpec.Description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityPctHigh
FixFieldSpec.Description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities > 1. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: EFPTrackingError
FixFieldSpec.Description: Eg Used in EFP trades 12% (EFP – Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: FairValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades

FixFieldSpec.Name: OutsideIndexPct
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ValueOfFutures
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityIndType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator. Valid values: 1 – 5day moving average 2 – 20 day moving average 3 – Normal Market Size 4 – Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical. Valid values: Y = True N = False

FixFieldSpec.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: CrossPercent
FixFieldSpec.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ProgRptReqs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports. Valid values: 1 – BuySide explicitly requests status using StatusRequest (Default) The sell-side firm can however, send a DONE status List Status Response in an unsolicited fashion 2 – SellSide periodically sends status using ListStatus. Period optionally specified in ProgressPeriod 3 – Real-time execution reports (to be discouraged)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don’t send status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: IncTaxInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross. Valid values: 1 - Net 2 - Gross

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumBidders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the type of trade. Valid values: R: Risk Trade G: VWAP Guarantee A: Agency J: Guaranteed Close

FixFieldSpec.Name: BasisPxType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the basis price type. Valid values: 2: Closing Price at morning session 3: Closing Price 4: Current price 5: SQ 6: VWAP through a day 7: VWAP through a morning session 8: VWAP through an afternoon session 9: VWAP through a day except YORI A: VWAP through a morning session except YORI B: VWAP through an afternoon session except YORI C: Strike D: Open Z: Others

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoBidComponents
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Country
FixFieldSpec.Description: ISO Country Code in field

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoStrikes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the price type. Valid values: 1 - Percentage 2 - per share (e.g. cents per share) 3 - Fixed Amount (absolute value)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayOrderQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty less all shares (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty = OrderQty – (CumQty - DayCumQty)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayCumQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of shares on a GT order that have traded today.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayAvgPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: The average price of shares on a GT order that have traded today.

FixFieldSpec.Name: GTBookingInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate. Valid values: 0 = book out all trades on day of execution 1 = accumulate executions until order is filled or expires 2 = accumulate until verbally notified otherwise

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoStrikes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListStatusType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the price type. Valid values: 1 – Ack 2 – Response 3 – Timed 4 – ExecStarted 5 – AllDone 6 – Alert

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetGrossInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross. Valid values: 1 - Net 2 - Gross

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListOrderStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order. Valid values: 1 – InBiddingProcess 2 – ReceivedForExecution 3 – Executing 4 – Canceling 5 – Alert 6 – All Done 7 – Reject

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExpireDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market’s business practices

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListExecInstType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst. Valid values: 1 - Immediate 2 - Wait for Execute Instruction (e.g. a List Execute message or phone call before proceeding with execution of the list)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to. Valid values: 1 - Order Cancel Request 2 - Order Cancel/Replace Request

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraTradeQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraTradeTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker. (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClearingFirm
FixFieldSpec.Description: Firm that will clear the trade. Used if different from the executing firm.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClearingAccount
FixFieldSpec.Description: Supplemental accounting information forwared to clearing house/firm.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow and LiquidityPctHigh in Currency.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MultiLegReportingType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securiteis, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.). Valid Values: 1 - Single Security (default if not specified) 2 - Individual leg of a multi-leg security 3 - Multi-leg security

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikeTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListStatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListStatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.
